Job Title: Cloud Solution Architect, Cloud & AI Platform
Ad Text:
Overview

With more than 45,000 employees and partners worldwide, the Customer Experience and Success (CE&S) organization is on a mission to empower customers to accelerate business value through differentiated customer experiences that leverage Microsoft’s products and services, ignited by our people and culture. We drive cross-company alignment and execution, ensuring that we consistently exceed customers’ expectations in every interaction, whether in-product, digital, or human-centered. CE&S is responsible for all up services across the company, including consulting, customer success, and support across Microsoft’s portfolio of solutions and products. Join CE&S and help us accelerate AI transformation for our customers and the world.

We are looking to hire a hands-on Cloud Solution Architect (CSA) to join our diverse, talented, high performance, and innovative team, focused on driving Infrastructure and Application Migrations via the Cloud Acceleration Factory. The Cloud Acceleration Factory is best suited for individuals that are highly technical, solution focused and have a passion for Project Management. The Cloud Acceleration Factory provides opportunity to drive feedback into Microsoft’s core product teams to help improve our platform.  

CSAs are senior individual contributors who operate globally and engage directly with customers. It is a hands-on technical and governance role spanning across design, build, and production. Candidates are expected to comfortably switch from a whiteboard to the keyboard. This is a truly exciting role that will feature unique and challenging technical problems to solve and to help our customers succeed.  

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Responsibilities

A Cloud Solution Architect (CSA) within the Cloud & AI Platforms Global Customer Success team focused on Securing the Modernization and Migration of customer workloads on Azure  

Customer-Centric Approach: 

Deliver Customer success on the Microsoft Cloud & AI Platforms with a special focus on helping customer migrate and modernize their workloads on Azure. 

Accountable for delivering innovative solutions to meet customer outcomes aligned to their TCO and ROI.  

Provide guidance and recommendations to customer to build resilient and secure solution architecture for their workloads on Azure. 

Business Impact: 

End-to-end ownership of Cloud Accelerate Factory (aka Factory) engagements to help customers jumpstart their Azure projects with no-cost deployment assistance. 

Provide Factory delivery oversight which includes being hands-on with delivery based on business requirements. 

Orchestrate effective execution of Partner + Factory delivery to scale reach and impact across all customer segments. 

Provide proactive management of Factory delivery risks through early identification of issues and mitigation. 

Unblock and Accelerate Factory delivery in the assigned territory of coverage. 

Technical Leadership: 

Maintain deep technical hands-on delivery skills for the assigned technical workloads, i.e.,Azure Infra – Azure IaaS, ALZ, Networking, Core Migrations, AVD, AVS (optional). And tools like Azure Migrate and DMS. 

Demonstrate technical depth in delivery by employing best practices and repeated IP to accelerate Factory delivery execution. 

Extract learning, actionable insights from Factory delivery execution by closing the loop with Technical Pillars colleagues to improve IP, offerings and process flows. 

Qualifications

Required Qualifications

A bachelor's degree in computer science, Information Technology, Engineering, Technology Management Or relevant qualifications

5+ years’ experience in cloud/Infra technologies, information technology (IT) consulting/support, systems administration, network operations, software development/support, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or Business Applications consulting OR equivalent experience.

Passion for technology and customer obsession.  

Displays strong stakeholder and relationship management across senior leaders, partners, and customers. 

Enthusiasm towards leading technologies and motivation to learn and grow. 

Excellent verbal and written communication, analytical and presentation skills in English. 

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, citizenship, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, immigration status, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran or military status, race, ethnicity, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable local laws, regulations and ordinances. If you need assistance with religious accommodations and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application process, read more about requesting accommodations.

Job Title: AI / Automation Consultant - $1,000 per day - Sydney
Ad Text:
AI Consultant - $1,000 per day - Sydney - 5 week Contract - Immediate Start - Greenfield Project - Gain real world AI "productionised" experience

Tech and Data people are looking for an AI & Automation Consultant to help shape the future of intelligent automation in a truly greenfield environment. This is your chance to design and deliver end to end AI/Automation solutions that will transform operations — including the automation of tenders and tendering processes. This is a hands-on, strategic, and high-impact consulting engagement. You'll work directly with senior stakeholders to identify opportunities for AI-driven automation, design innovative solutions, influence strategy and guide through to delivery.

What You'll Do

Lead the strategy, architecture, and implementation of AI & automation initiatives from the ground up.
Work with business leaders to identify and prioritise automation opportunities across processes and systems.
Develop proof-of-concepts, prototypes, and scalable solutions using modern AI/ML tools, RPA platforms, and workflow automation.
Focus initially on streamlining the tender/tendering process, then expand into broader business areas.
Act as the trusted advisor for executives and teams, clearly communicating complex technical ideas in business-friendly language.
Deliver measurable improvements in efficiency, accuracy, and speed across business operations.
What We're Looking For

An AI/Automation Consultant or Solution Architect with strong consulting experience.
Proven expertise in end-to-end delivery: from opportunity discovery and business case development to design, build, and deployment.
Deep understanding of automation platforms (e.g., UiPath, Power Automate, Blue Prism, etc.) and AI/ML tools (e.g., Azure/OpenAI, AWS, GCP).
Ability to bridge business and technical teams — strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills are a must.
Experience working in greenfield environments where you've built strategies and solutions from scratch.
Background in tender/tendering process automation or similar large-scale workflow optimisation is highly desirable.
Why Join

5 week contract with the potential for extension.
Work on a high-visibility project with a direct impact on efficiency and innovation.
Shape the AI/automation roadmap from the ground up.
Immediate start in Sydney - hybrid/onsite flexibility.
This is an exceptional opportunity for someone who thrives on solving complex problems, leading innovation, and delivering tangible business outcomes.

Our client is an international defence supplier, who design, manufacture and integrate communications solutions for Australian and global customers. They are looking to bolster their systems engineering capability supporting a number of projects across the Land and Air sectors.

Individuals with experience across the entire systems engineering life-cycle (Design and Review, V&V, Test & Integration, Requirements Management) will be highly suitable.


The Role:

Enforce design, system and specifications as required.
Establishing test plans & procedures and test analysis
Implementation, integration, verification, and validation
System definition/high level, preliminary and detailed design
Provide requirements analysis and management with the use of software management tools such as; DOORs and/or UML.



Experience Required:

3-5 years' experience as a Systems Engineer or more
Engineering Degree in either of the following disciplines: Electrical, Communications, Electronics, Mechatronics, Software and/or Hardware
Experience in systems architecture, design & development, and test & evaluation.
Australian Citizenship essential; current or Reinstatable clearance ideal
Defence industry experience desirable.


Please only apply if you hold Australian Citizenship, can obtain and maintain a Defence Security Clearance and US International Traffic in Arms Regulations clearance procedures.

If you think you match the above criteria, please apply in Word format only. PDF is also accepted.

Kinexus is the leading supplier for recruitment solutions to the Australian Defence Industry bringing intelligent connections and ideas together to better our sovereign nations capabilities in the field, at sea or in the air.

All applications should include your resume as a word document.

For more information, visit our website www.kinexus.com.au or contact Lewis Landau on 0422 572 745.

Multiple Operations Data Engineers are required to support and maintain enterprise data assets across a modern cloud-based data platform. These roles play a key part in ensuring the reliability, performance, and operational stability of data services, supporting both business-as-usual (BAU) delivery and critical processing cycles.

The positions focus on operational support of data pipelines, month-end processing, and responding to data-related requests, while ensuring service level agreements (SLAs) are consistently met across the platform.


Key Responsibilities

Support and maintain data assets across cloud data lake, cloud EDW, legacy EDW, and analytics platforms
Provide Level 2/3 technical support across AWS, Control-M, Snowflake, Teradata (legacy), and ETL-based integration solutions
Support daily data delivery processes and month-end operational workloads
Develop and maintain SQL-based analytical and ETL code
Monitor and manage scheduling workflows using Control-M or similar tools
Work with file transfer solutions such as GoAnywhere or equivalent
Apply DevOps practices and tools in line with established delivery processes
Maintain system and technical documentation
Analyse, size, prioritise, and queue work items
Collaborate with data consumers, database developers, testers, and IT support teams
Drive continuous improvement in coding standards, delivery practices, and documentation, including knowledge sharing and training
Essential Skills & Experience

Strong experience with AWS data engineering services including Glue, S3, Lambda, EC2, and RDS
Proven experience designing and developing data pipelines using ETL/ELT frameworks
Hands-on experience with Snowflake (cloud EDW) and/or Teradata (on-prem EDW)
High level of programming capability, particularly in Python
Experience with Control-M orchestration, monitoring, or similar scheduling tools
Strong background in operational support and BAU environments
Desirable Experience

Infrastructure-as-code exposure using CloudFormation or Terraform
Experience with ETL tools such as DBT, Talend, Informatica, or similar
Advanced SQL capability
Exposure to SAS platforms (Base, Enterprise Guide, or SAS Viya)

This role will be offered as an initial 12 month contract + opportunity to extend.

Multiple roles are available in Sydney and Melbourne and are due to start early February 2026.

To apply please send your resume or contact Nat on 0430 292 875 or natalie@blackroc.co

Our client is a leading Defence consultancy with a national presence and will be seeking multiple Modelling and Simulation Engineers for upcoming contract opportunities, across the Maritime and Aerospace sectors.

These roles will involve Systems Modelling, Software Modelling and Simulation, and Verification & Validation (V&V).

Candidates with Defence experience and backgrounds in Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, or Software Engineering are encouraged to apply. The required years of experience are flexible, and we welcome applications from both mid-level and senior professionals.

These positions are expected to start in February depending on candidate availability and processing timelines.

Responsibilities:

Integrate MATLAB/Simulink models into custom simulation environments (C++) and test integration outcomes.
Review simulation results, providing guidance and support tools.
Design and conduct tests to validate individual models and the overall system.
Create detailed documentation, including report writing and presenting results.
Develop new models and execute existing ones using various software tools.
Plan, integrate, and test the model integration process, including defining steps and documenting results.

Requirements:

Experience working on Defence platform systems or related applications.
Strong background in modelling and simulation, software development, or numerical analysis.
Familiarity with MATLAB/Simulink, C++, and modern simulation tools.
Understanding of Radar and Electromagnetic technologies
Experience with CUDA
Proficient in both Windows and Linux development environments.
NV1 security clearance or higher.

Please note: Recruitment for this position will resume after Jan 12th.

All applications should include your resume as a word document.

For more information, visit our website, www.kinexus.com.au or contact Ellen Hanratty on 03 9982 0303.
